news.title: How 2024 shaped architecture and what lies ahead in 2025
news.para: 2024 highlighted the rising need for design that puts environmental sensitivity and human well-being first in the post-pandemic world.

news.title: Pune: Housing societies in Wakad receive notices over pending NA taxes
news.para: The state govt, in October 2024, in a cabinet meeting, decided to abolish the non-agricultural (NA) tax for properties.

news.title: GHMC to levy huge penalty to deter illegal constructions in Hyderabad
news.para: The Greater Hyderabad Municipal Corporation (GHMC) is planning to launch an online portal to monitor illegal constructions across the city. GHMC will impose severe penalties and a notation on the encumbrance certificate (EC).

news.title: Another FIR registered against Shine City's director in Lucknow
news.para: So far, about 150 FIRs have been registered at different police stations across the city in connection with the multi-crore scam, with 80 complaints lodged at Gomtinagar police station alone.

news.title: Home prices in Hong Kong edge up 0.07% in November 2024
news.para: Home prices in Hong Kong, one of the world's most unaffordable cities, have tumbled nearly 30% from their 2021 peak, hurt by higher mortgage rates, an outflow of professionals and a weak market outlook.

news.title: Kerala government exempts Kochi Metro Rail from property tax
news.para: KMRL had filed cases against the corporation and nearby local bodies in the high court, challenging the property tax demand notices for its station buildings and related structures.

news.title: Navi Mumbai Airport to be functional from early next fiscal
news.para: "Our ambition is to do the commercial inauguration of the airport by April 17," Adani Airport Holdings Ltd CEO Arun Bansal told media after the successful trial landing of the first civil passenger aircraft.

news.title: Telangana government to mandate land coordinates to curb registration irregularities
news.para: This move follows provisions for the digital survey and rough mapping of land under the Bhu Bharathi (Right of Records) Act, which replaced the RoR Act, 2020.

news.title: Proposed IT Park in Ujjain to come up as plug and play
news.para: Approximately 30 IT industries are anticipated to operate in the park, generating an estimated direct employment of 500 positions and exceeding 1,000 indirect jobs.

news.title: Nashik civic body & smart city corporation should work in cohesive manner: NMC chief
news.para: She said govt agencies should start work on development projects in the core areas of the city instead of waiting for the appointment of consultants for the project.

news.title: Bombay HC stays allotment of 80 transit flats by Mhada
news.para: The petition said Bombay Dyeing Mill (Spring Mill) Wadala, over 33,000 sq m land was handed over to MHADA from 09.12.2014 in which 5,136 flats were reserved for the mill workers which BMC too approved.

news.title: MahaRERA orders builder to pay home buyer interest on delayed flat
news.para: The allottee alleged that after booking, it was disclosed that the said flats of the complainant were under mortgage. However, the flats were falsely mentioned as “unsold units” in the disclosure statement of the project by the promoter.

news.title: Two zones upgraded, but it means higher cost of living in Haryana
news.para: These zones — categorised under the Haryana Development and Regulation of Urban Areas Rules, 1976 — were initially deemed to have limited urban growth capacity.

news.title: Jaipur metro expansion planned to new destinations
news.para: Officials said that following a recent review meeting of the UDH department, chaired by chief minister Bhajan Lal Sharma, there are plans to expand the proposed Line 2 from Vidhyadhar Nagar to Chomu and from Sitapura to two different directions: Jagatpura and Chaksu.

news.title: Kanpur development body traces over four hectares of land illegally occupied by people
news.para: KDA is presently engaged in expanding its land bank, and while conducting a land audit during this process, the land department discovered property valued at Rs 1.69 billion that had been fraudulently mutated in the names of occupants.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Mixed-used project approved on Sabarmati riverfront's commercial plot
news.para: ​The Sabarmati Riverfront Development Corporation Limited (SRFDCL), a special purpose vehicle of the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC), issued a Request for Proposal (RFP) for the sale of development rights.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body to digitise TS-1 certificates
news.para: MC submitted a proposal during a meeting of the technical advisory committee, which approved it. Thereafter, the proposal was sent to the local bodies department for final approval.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Neopolis IT township project gets union government's green light
news.para: Union minister of housing and urban affairs Manohar Lal Khattar assured that the OAGC project is under active consideration and that Neopolis would soon receive formal approval.

news.title: Centre puts Global City plans on hold over real estate tilt in Kochi
news.para: The decision comes after concerns were raised that the project's focus was more on residential and real estate developments than on industrial undertakings, as stipulated in the regulations.

news.title: Over 220 cases of illegal sand trading lodged in coastal Karnataka in 2024
news.para: The majority of illegal sand transportation cases were reported across various police stations in Dakshina Kannada district in 2024.
